"{\"uid\": \"theguardian.com-environment-article-2024-jul-17-brisbane-olympics-2032-local-food-consumption-targets\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Sustainable food experts want to revive fragile supply chains by using the games to 'catalyse conservation'  Sustainable food advocates are calling for the amount of locally grown produce supplied to Brisbane to increase by 30% by the2032 Brisbane Olympic Gamesto strengthenthe city's \\\"fragile\\\" supply chains.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 309, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 200, \"end\": 208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9999976683184185, \"rank\": 2.328672534604418e-06, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But first, they have to figure out how much ofBrisbane's food is currently grown locally.\", \"from\": 311, \"to\": 400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"moonshot\\\" goal will be discussed at the inaugural south-eastQueenslandfood summit later this month.\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Emma-Kate Rose, the event organiser and director of the Food Connect Foundation, said the target is aimed at addressing a laundry list of systemic issues threatening the reliability of national food distribution system, including increasing extreme weather events which cancut off elongated supply lines.\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 812, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 518, \"end\": 522, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\", \"score\": 0.999954286953971, \"rank\": 4.570366528536251e-05, \"text\": \"Rose\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up to receive Guardian Australia's fortnightly Rural Network email newsletter  \\\"Our question is, how do we create a more resilient food system in the long term?\\\"\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 833, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Guardian Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Guardian_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rose said.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 991, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\", \"score\": 0.999954286953971, \"rank\": 4.570366528536251e-05, \"text\": \"Rose\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are using the Olympics as a way to catalyse that conservation.\\\"\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1059, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sourcing food locally reduces transportation costs and emissions, makes for fresher and more nutritious food, and meanssupply chains are shorterand less vulnerable to shocks like natural disasters or pandemics.\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1271, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Like Sydney and Melbourne, Brisbane's peri-urban fringes contain highly productive agricultural land suitable for intensive cropping and horticulture.\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1423, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1278, \"end\": 1284, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9995962451745991, \"rank\": 0.00040376529234705726, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 1289, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999983575030302, \"rank\": 1.52951979539703e-06, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 1300, \"end\": 1308, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9999976683184185, \"rank\": 2.328672534604418e-06, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These regions historically produced much of the food consumed in the cities.But figuring out how much food they produce now - or where the produce ends up - is \\\"near impossible\\\", Rose said.\", \"from\": 1425, \"to\": 1614, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1604, \"end\": 1608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\", \"score\": 0.999954286953971, \"rank\": 4.570366528536251e-05, \"text\": \"Rose\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rose\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is different numbers floating around depending on who you talk to, but we do not have that baseline,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 1616, \"to\": 1734, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if a baseline is determined, meeting the ambitious goal will be an uphill battle.\", \"from\": 1736, \"to\": 1822, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A 2016 report by Foodprint Melbourne estimated that the Melbourne food bowlhad the capacity to produce41% of the city's total food needs.\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1961, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1851, \"end\": 1860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999983575030302, \"rank\": 1.52951979539703e-06, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 1880, \"end\": 1889, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999983575030302, \"rank\": 1.52951979539703e-06, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But that land is shrinking.\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1989, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By 2040, the report predicted, the fertile plains would produce just 18% of the city's food needsasprime agricultural land is consumed by the construction of sprawling housing estates.\", \"from\": 1990, \"to\": 2174, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's very concerning, there is good reasons why we want to be growing food around cities in the future,\\\" the report's lead author, Dr Rachel Carey, said.\", \"from\": 2176, \"to\": 2330, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2311, \"end\": 2317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\", \"score\": 0.9753006481816928, \"rank\": 0.019319113874073857, \"text\": \"Rachel\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachel_Green\"}, {\"begin\": 2318, \"end\": 2323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 0.9246992114370657, \"rank\": 0.08143273794428518, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sydney is faring even worse.Another studyfound the farmland remaining around the city is only capable of meeting20% of the city's overall food needs, with more losses expected if urban sprawl continues unabated.\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2332, \"end\": 2338, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9995962451745991, \"rank\": 0.00040376529234705726, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Sydney is kind of where Melbourne could be heading if we do not change our policies,\\\" Carey said.\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2545, \"end\": 2551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"score\": 0.9995962451745991, \"rank\": 0.00040376529234705726, \"text\": \"Sydney\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sydney\"}, {\"begin\": 2569, \"end\": 2578, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"score\": 0.9999983575030302, \"rank\": 1.52951979539703e-06, \"text\": \"Melbourne\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melbourne\"}, {\"begin\": 2631, \"end\": 2636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"score\": 0.9246992114370657, \"rank\": 0.08143273794428518, \"text\": \"Carey\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mariah_Carey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up toThe Rural Network  Subscribe to Calla Wahlquist's fortnightly update on Australian rural and regional affairs  after newsletter promotion  Last year, aNew South Wales inquiry into food production and supplyfound productive agricultural land in peri-urban areas was under increasing threat from development.\", \"from\": 2644, \"to\": 2960, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2726, \"end\": 2736, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"score\": 0.9943524785633291, \"rank\": 0.005676225205184119, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australian_Government\"}, {\"begin\": 2815, \"end\": 2820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Wales\", \"score\": 0.7262813948241769, \"rank\": 0.3768767960811602, \"text\": \"Wales\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Wales\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Wales\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Afederal inquiryhad similar findings, recommending the protection of agricultural land from urban sprawl.\", \"from\": 2962, \"to\": 3067, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It recommended the governmentascertain the optimal location of food distribution centres and develop a national food supply chain map to better understand the journey of food from paddock to plate.\", \"from\": 3068, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Associate Prof Andrea Gaynor, an environmental historian from the University of Western Australia, said that while there are benefits to locally-grown food, it can still be vulnerable to supply chain shocks.\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3474, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3267, \"end\": 3281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associate_professor\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Associate Prof\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associate_professor\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associate_professor\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think the idea of bringing agriculture closer to the city is about making it smaller scale, adaptive andcommunity focused agriculture,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3624, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That gives children the chance to see how food can be grown, for urban wastes to be used, it can encourage circular economy type behaviours and reduce waste.\\\"\", \"from\": 3625, \"to\": 3784, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gaynor said colonial Australia had a long history of growing fruit and vegetable in or near cities, but after the second world war, those habits began to deteriorate as large-scalecommercial horticulture operations were developed and cities expanded.\", \"from\": 3786, \"to\": 4036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3798, \"end\": 3816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Australia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.3650869159203275e-35, \"text\": \"colonial Australia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Australia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Australia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A report from afood supply inquiryin Victoria, focused on the impact of population growth on the state's food supply, is due in November.\", \"from\": 4038, \"to\": 4175, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4075, \"end\": 4083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_Victoria\", \"score\": 0.9481886516061527, \"rank\": 0.024126528269089197, \"text\": \"Victoria\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_Victoria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Queen_Victoria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sign up for the Rural Network email newsletter  Join the Rural Network group on Facebook to be part of the community\", \"from\": 4177, \"to\": 4293, \"entities\": []}]}"